  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hearts and Hands for Haiti has eight rural primary schools in the region of Gonaives, Haiti, with an enrollment of more than 1,800 students. They provide a nutritious meal on as many school days as possible during the school year. The students come from low-income, rural families where they often do not receive food on a regular basis. Ladies from the community volunteer to prepare the food for the schools.
The children&apos;s home of Hearts and Hands for Haiti has been open since 1997 and has consistently had 70 youth living in the home. These children are all from very destitute situations, many of them brought by an ailing grandparent. These children are nurtured by a loving staff and grow up receiving education, vocational training and spiritual discipleship.  
www.heartsandhandsforhaiti.org</narrative>
  </description>
